The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the problem of dominating sets in graphs. This falls under the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Graph Theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the complexity of recognizing well-dominated graphs, which is a topic in Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
